"Last week I also re-issued Made of Bricks on PINK VINYL! OMGEEEE!! Sold out of it on kickstarter in 2 hours! And loads of you have been asking about it since, so we are doing what we can to see if we can get some more made up, so keep your eyes peeled and keep checking my twitter for news!! I also announced a second date at Shepherds Bush Empire!! We sold out of the first date so fast that we are celebrating with a second! Im so excited about that tour, I start rehearsing all the Made of Bricks stuff in a couple weeks. Gonna be filled with such nostalgia.

We also played a show at the Salisbury Art Centre last week, which is where Emma, in my band, grew up playing. We literally played a night with a bunch of kids, it was amazing, its so important to give back where you can and to stay engaged with the local community. Its so powerful. There was an aristocats performance and a dance group and a bunch of cool teen bands and there were the cutest little girls in the front row at the show who all wanna learn guitar now. We spent the weekend at Emmas place in the countryside and had piano singalongs and breakfast in the garden and watched zombie moves and stood in cow poop and saw stonehenge, spiritual times. Perfect location to land in for earth day!!"

WOW! I hit my kickstarter target!!! Thank you so much for supporting me so much already! 

Fuck it, let's set a stretch goal! I now know I can release the record but let's see how far I can take this. Touring is so important to me, it would be amazing to be able to travel to as many places as possible with this record and to play this new music whilst staring into your sparkly and magical eyes!! 

So my new goal is to get to 2,000 backers. If we get to 2,000 backers I will send an unreleased NEW SONG to my Kickstarter fam only. We're a family, and it's all about family, just like Fast and the Furious, my favourite franchise.

Thank you so much for your kindness and support from the bottom of my cold, dead heart <3

Hi! 
Yesterday I launched my Kickstarter. I have a 4th album that I am keen to finish and put out into the world. I decided that I want my fans to be my record label as I don't want to have to change my art and looks to fit into what record labels have seemed to want from me. To me, working w you is far more inspiring and real. YOU have continued to support me, allowed me to experiment and grow and I love you for that. From MySpace to here just makes sense. Thank you for showing up for me and all that you already do. If you want my fourth record please fund it and pre order the record and get special behind the scenes shit exclusive to those who pledge. I'm Buffy, you're mr. pointy...let's slay ! Lol
